<div class="row" style="height: 100%">
  <div class="col-sm-4" style="height: 100%">

    <label for="snapshot-area">Write a program that will read in integers and output their average. Stop reading when the value 99999 is

input. Do not include the value 99999 in the average.</label>
    <label for="snapshot-area">Please construct your code here. We are more interested in your work process than your codeâ€™s

correctness. Your solution does not need to be correct to be entered in the lottery.</label>
    <div style="height: 90%" class="form-control" id="snapshot-area" onpaste="return false"></div>

    <%= hidden_field_tag 'access_key', @access_key %>

    <div class="actions" style="margin-top: 5%;">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary", id='submit-solution'> Submit Solution </button>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/ace/1.2.6/ace.js" integrity="sha256-xrr4HH5eSY+cFz4SH7ja/LaAi9qcEdjMpeMP49/iOLs=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
<script>
    var editor = ace.edit("snapshot-area");
    editor.setTheme("ace/theme/monokai");
    editor.getSession().setMode("ace/mode/c_cpp");
    editor.setOptions({
      fontSize: "16pt",
    });
    editor.resize()
</script>